rdf:Description.music:description:
Roger Hodgson wrote and composed the songs listed above on the Breakfast in America Album. Though all the above songs that Roger recorded with Supertramp were credited equally Hodgson/Davies, that does not reflect how it really was. Roger actually wrote his songs while he was alone and many of his biggest hits were songs he had written before he met Rick and co-founded the band. Roger and Rick actually wrote separately, though they continued to share writer's credit. Of course, it would have been Roger's preference if he'd had better advice and had all the songs he wrote in just his name and the ones Rick wrote just in Rick's name so there would not be so much confusion about the difference in artistic, lyrical and musical styles of each songwriter and composer.
The Roger Hodgson Store is the only place you can buy directly from the artist and get his autographed CD's. Visit www.RogerHodgsonStore.com
Get your own autographed copy of this CD at rogerhodgson.spinshop.com/details/1517…p;wId=151757

rdf:Description.music:description: Get the kids in (and then out of) the kitchen on Christmas day with some yummy Christmas pancakes. Find the recipe here: po.st/LBXmasBlog2 Our host Isabel and chef Marika Gauci are back with another tummy tempting recipe. Listen to Marika baking Christmas Morning Sweet Cranberry Pancakes with her three year old daughter, Phaedra. You can also enjoy Christmas memories from our very own Ladybird team and Radio 6 presenter and dad Shaun Keaveny. Special celebrity guest Jo Whiley also pops in to offer cooking tips for little ones. But a Ladybird podcast wouldn't be complete without storytime and this one is from Hansel and Gretel.
